ne.py`) with no raw sqlite3 cruft\\n\\n## Problem Statement\\n\\n`database.py` was kept because 18+ test files use its `db()` context manager for raw sqlite3 setup/assertions. Once tests are migrated, the file can be deleted. `db_engine.py` also has a deprecated `init_sqlmodel_tables()` no-op that should be removed.\\n\\n## Solution Statement\\n\\n1. Add a `session_db` fixture to `conftest.py` that yields an SQLModel `Session` (backed by the same temp DB as `patched_db`)\\n2. Convert all `with db() as conn: conn.execute(raw SQL)` calls in tests to SQLModel ORM operations\\n3. Remove the `import backend.database as db_module` and `monkeypatch.setattr(db_module, \\\"DB_PATH\\\", ...)` lines from `conftest.py`\\n4. Remove `init_sqlmodel_tables()` from `db_engine.py`\\n5. Delete `backend/database.py`\\n\\n## Metadata\\n\\n| Field | Value |\\n|-------|-------|\\n| Type | BUG_FIX / REFACTOR |\\n| Complexity | HIGH |\\n| Systems Affected | `backend/database.py`, `backend/db_engine.py`, `backend/tests/conftest.py`, 18 test files |\\n| Dependencies | SQLModel (already in use), pytest (already in use) |\\n| Estimated Tasks | 6 |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## UX Design\\n\\nNo user-facing changes. This is internal test infrastructure cleanup.\\n\\n### Before State\\n\\n```\\n╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\\n║                              BEFORE STATE                                      ║\\n╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\\n║                                                                               ║\\n║   Test setup:  from backend.database import db                                ║\\n║                with db() as conn:                                             ║\\n║                    conn.execute(\\\"INSERT INTO things ...\\\")  ← raw sqlite3      ║\\n║                                                                               ║\\n║   conftest.py: patches DB_PATH in backend.database                            ║\\n║                patches engine in backend.db_engine                            ║\\n║                → Two separate patches needed to keep them in sync             ║\\n║                                                                               ║\\n║   db_engine.py: has deprecated init_sqlmodel_tables() no-op                  ║\\n║                                                                               ║\\n╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\\n```\\n\\n### After State\\n\\n```\\n╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\\n║                               AFTER STATE                                      ║\\n╠═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\\n║                                                                               ║\\n║   Test setup:  from backend.db_models import ThingRecord                      ║\\n║                session.add(ThingRecord(title=\\\"...\\\", ...))   ← SQLModel ORM   ║\\n║                                                                               ║\\n║   conftest.py: patches only engine in backend.db_engine                       ║\\n║                provides session_db fixture for direct ORM access              ║\\n║                → Single source of truth                                       ║\\n║                                                                               ║\\n║   db_engine.py: no deprecated functions                                       ║\\n║   database.py: DELETED                                                        ║\\n║                                                                               ║\\n╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\\n```\\n\\n### Interaction Changes\\n\\n| Location | Before | After | User Impact |\\n|----------|--------|-------|-------------|\\n| `backend/database.py` | Exists with `DB_PATH`, `db()` | Deleted | N/A (internal) |\\n| `backend/db_engine.py` | Has `init_sqlmodel_tables()` no-op | Removed | N/A |\\n| `backend/tests/conftest.py` | Patches `db_module.DB_PATH` | No `database` import | Simpler fixture |\\n| 18 test files | `from backend.database import db` | SQLModel session ops | Tests still pass |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Mandatory Reading\\n\\n**CRITICAL: Implementation agent MUST read these files before starting any task:**\\n\\n| Priority | File | Lines | Why Read This |\\n|----------|------|-------|---------------|\\n| P0 | `backend/database.py` | all (37 lines) | File being deleted — understand `db()` and `DB_PATH` |\\n| P0 | `backend/tests/conftest.py` | all | `patched_db` fixture to update; `session_db` to add |\\n| P0 | `backend/db_engine.py` | 87-109 | `init_sqlmodel_tables()` to remove; `get_session` pattern to mirror |\\n| P1 | `backend/db_models.py` | 1-60 | Model classes for ORM inserts (ThingRecord, UserRecord, etc.) |\\n| P1 | `backend/tests/test_things.py` | 255-270 | Example `db()` usage to convert: PRAGMA + INSERT |\\n| P1 | `backend/tests/test_summarization.py` | 1-50 | Heavy raw SQL usage pattern to convert |\\n| P2 | `backend/tests/test_chat_pipeline.py` | 250-540 | Most `db()` call sites (10 usages) — largest migration target |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Patterns to Mirror\\n\\n**ORM INSERT PATTERN (replace raw conn.execute INSERT):**\\n```python\\n# SOURCE: backend/tests/conftest.py:77-80\\n# COPY THIS PATTERN:\\nwith Session(test_engine) as session:\\n    session.add(ThingTypeRecord(id=name, name=name, icon=icon))\\n    session.commit()\\n```\\n\\n**ORM SELECT PATTERN (replace raw conn.execute SELECT):**\\n```python\\n# SOURCE: backend/db_engine.py:87-90\\n# COPY THIS PATTERN:\\nfrom sqlmodel import Session, select\\nwith Session(engine) as session:\\n    result = session.exec(select(ThingRecord).where(ThingRecord.id == thing_id)).first()\\n```\\n\\n**PRAGMA FOREIGN_KEYS OFF (special case — test_things.py):**\\n```python\\n# The only PRAGMA usage in test_things.py inserts an orphan relationship.\\n# Replace with: temporarily disable FK via SQLAlchemy event or direct connection\\nfrom sqlalchemy import event, text\\nwith Session(engine) as session:\\n    session.exec(text(\\\"PRAGMA foreign_keys=OFF\\\"))\\n    session.add(ThingRelationshipRecord(id=rel_id, from_thing_id=from_id, to_thing_id=to_id, relationship_type=rel_type))\\n    session.commit()\\n    session.exec(text(\\\"PRAGMA foreign_keys=ON\\\"))\\n```\\n\\n**SESSION FIXTURE PATTERN:**\\n```python\\n# SOURCE: backend/tests/conftest.py:85-91 (test engine pattern)\\n# COPY THIS PATTERN:\\n@pytest.fixture()\\ndef session_db(patched_db, tmp_db_path):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Yield a SQLModel Session for the test database.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    from sqlmodel import Session, create_engine\\n    test_engine = create_engine(f\\\"sqlite:///{tmp_db_path}\\\", connect_args={\\\"check_same_thread\\\": False})\\n    with Session(test_engine) as session:\\n        yield session\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Files to Change\\n\\n| File | Action | Justification |\\n|------|--------|---------------|\\n| `backend/database.py` | DELETE | No callers after test migration |\\n| `backend/db_engine.py` | UPDATE | Remove `init_sqlmodel_tables()` no-op (lines 94-108) |\\n| `backend/tests/conftest.py` | UPDATE | Remove `db_module` import + `DB_PATH` patch; add `session_db` fixture |\\n| `backend/tests/test_things.py` | UPDATE | 1 `db()` usage → SQLModel text() PRAGMA + ORM insert |\\n| `backend/tests/test_summarization.py` | UPDATE | Multiple raw SQL → ORM operations |\\n| `backend/tests/test_chat_pipeline.py` | UPDATE | 10 `db()` usages → ORM operations (largest file) |\\n| `backend/tests/test_auth.py` | UPDATE | 2 inline `from backend.database import db` → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_merge.py` | UPDATE | top-level import + usages → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_sweep_patterns.py` | UPDATE | top-level import + usages → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_staleness.py` | UPDATE | 3 inline imports → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_sweep_scheduler.py` | UPDATE | 7 inline imports → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_mcp_server.py` | UPDATE | 1 inline import → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_reasoning_agent.py` | UPDATE | 2 inline imports → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_sweep_reflection.py` | UPDATE | top-level import → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_morning_briefing.py` | UPDATE | 2 inline imports → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_conflict_detector.py` | UPDATE | top-level import → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_chat_summarization_pipeline.py` | UPDATE | top-level import → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_personality_preferences.py` | UPDATE | 4 inline imports → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_possessive_dedup.py` | UPDATE | top-level import → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_preference_sweep.py` | UPDATE | top-level import → ORM |\\n| `backend/tests/test_sweep.py` | UPDATE | top-level import → ORM |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## NOT Building (Scope Limits)\\n\\n- Not refactoring test logic — only replacing the database access mechanism\\n- Not migrating tests to async — keep existing sync/async patterns as-is\\n- Not removing `database_supabase.py` — it does not exist in this codebase\\n- Not removing `user_filter()` from `auth.py` — it does not exist (already removed)\\n- Not removing `_exec()` from `db_engine.py` — it does not exist (already removed)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step-by-Step Tasks\\n\\nExecute in order. Each task is atomic and independently verifiable.\\n\\n### Task 1: UPDATE `backend/db_engine.py`\\n\\n- **ACTION**: UPDATE existing file\\n- **IMPLEMENT**: Remove the `init_sqlmodel_tables()` function (lines 94-108 inclusive). Also remove the blank line at line 93.\\n- **MIRROR**: N/A — pure deletion\\n- **VALIDATE**: `cd backend && python -c \\\"from backend.db_engine import get_session, engine, user_filter_clause, user_filter_text; print('OK')\\\"` — must print OK\\n\\n### Task 2: UPDATE `backend/tests/conftest.py`\\n\\n- **ACTION**: UPDATE existing file\\n- **IMPLEMENT**:\\n  1. Remove lines importing `backend.database`:\\n     ```python\\n     import backend.database as db_module\\n     ```\\n  2. Remove the line:\\n     ```python\\n     monkeypatch.setattr(db_module, \\\"DB_PATH\\\", tmp_db_path)\\n     ```\\n  3. Add a `session_db` fixture after `patched_db` that yields a SQLModel Session backed by the test engine:\\n     ```python\\n     @pytest.fixture()\\n     def session_db(patched_db, tmp_db_path: Path):\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"Yield a SQLModel Session for the test database.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         from sqlmodel import Session, create_engine\\n         test_engine = create_engine(\\n             f\\\"sqlite:///{tmp_db_path}\\\",\\n             connect_args={\\\"check_same_thread\\\": False},\\n         )\\n         with Session(test_engine) as session:\\n             yield session\\n     ```\\n- **GOTCHA**: `patched_db` already patches `engine_module.engine` — the `session_db` fixture uses the same `tmp_db_path` so they share the same DB file\\n- **VALIDATE**: `cd /path/to/backend && python -c \\\"import backend.tests.conftest\\\"` — no ImportError\\n\\n### Task 3: Read each of the 18 test files and convert `db()` usages\\n\\nFor each file, the pattern is:\\n- Remove `from backend.database import db` (top-level or inline)\\n- Replace `with db() as conn: conn.execute(...)` with equivalent SQLModel Session operations\\n\\n**Conversion strategy per usage type:**\\n\\n**INSERT operations** → Use `session.add(ModelRecord(...))` + `session.commit()`\\n```python\\n# BEFORE:\\nwith db() as conn:\\n    conn.execute(\\\"INSERT INTO things (id, title, ...) VALUES (?, ?, ...)\\\", (id, title, ...))\\n\\n# AFTER (use session_db fixture OR create a session from engine_module.engine):\\nfrom backend.db_models import ThingRecord\\nimport backend.db_engine as engine_module\\nfrom sqlmodel import Session\\nwith Session(engine_module.engine) as session:\\n    session.add(ThingRecord(id=id, title=title, ...))\\n    session.commit()\\n```\\n\\n**SELECT operations** → Use `session.exec(select(Model).where(...))`\\n```python\\n# BEFORE:\\nwith db() as conn:\\n    row = conn.execute(\\\"SELECT * FROM things WHERE id = ?\\\", (id,)).fetchone()\\n\\n# AFTER:\\nfrom sqlmodel import Session, select\\nfrom backend.db_models import ThingRecord\\nimport backend.db_engine as engine_module\\nwith Session(engine_module.engine) as session:\\n    thing = session.exec(select(ThingRecord).where(ThingRecord.id == id)).first()\\n```\\n\\n**PRAGMA operations** (only in test_things.py) → Use `text()` via Session\\n```python\\n# BEFORE (test_things.py:261-268):\\nwith db() as conn:\\n    conn.execute(\\\"PRAGMA foreign_keys=OFF\\\")\\n    conn.execute(\\\"INSERT INTO thing_relationships ...\\\")\\n    conn.execute(\\\"PRAGMA foreign_keys=ON\\\")\\n\\n# AFTER:\\nfrom sqlalchemy import text\\nfrom sqlmodel import Session\\nimport backend.db_engine as engine_module\\nfrom backend.db_models import ThingRelationshipRecord\\nwith Session(engine_module.engine) as session:\\n    session.exec(text(\\\"PRAGMA foreign_keys=OFF\\\"))\\n    session.add(ThingRelationshipRecord(id=rel_id, from_thing_id=from_id, to_thing_id=to_id, relationship_type=rel_type))\\n    session.commit()\\n    session.exec(text(\\\"PRAGMA foreign_keys=ON\\\"))\\n```\\n\\n**Per-file task list** (read each file first, then convert):\\n\\n- [ ] `test_things.py` — 1 usage (PRAGMA + INSERT)\\n- [ ] `test_summarization.py` — ~10 usages (heavy raw SQL with helper functions)\\n- [ ] `test_chat_pipeline.py` — 10 usages (largest, inline imports)\\n- [ ] `test_auth.py` — 2 usages (inline imports)\\n- [ ] `test_merge.py` — top-level import\\n- [ ] `test_sweep_patterns.py` — top-level import\\n- [ ] `test_staleness.py` — 3 usages\\n- [ ] `test_sweep_scheduler.py` — 7 usages\\n- [ ] `test_mcp_server.py` — 1 usage\\n- [ ] `test_reasoning_agent.py` — 2 usages\\n- [ ] `test_sweep_reflection.py` — top-level import\\n- [ ] `test_morning_briefing.py` — 2 usages\\n- [ ] `test_conflict_detector.py` — top-level import\\n- [ ] `test_chat_summarization_pipeline.py` — top-level import\\n- [ ] `test_personality_preferences.py` — 4 usages\\n- [ ] `test_possessive_dedup.py` — top-level import\\n- [ ] `test_preference_sweep.py` — top-level import\\n- [ ] `test_sweep.py` — top-level import\\n\\n- **VALIDATE** after each file: `cd backend && python -m pytest tests/<file>.py -x -q 2>&1 | tail -5`\\n\\n### Task 4: Verify no remaining `database.py` imports\\n\\n- **ACTION**: Grep verification\\n- **IMPLEMENT**: Run:\\n  ```bash\\n  grep -rn \\\"from backend.database\\\\|from .database\\\\|import database\\\" backend/ --include=\\\"*.py\\\" | grep -v \\\"__pycache__\\\"\\n  ```\\n- **EXPECT**: Zero results\\n\\n### Task 5: DELETE `backend/database.py`\\n\\n- **ACTION**: Delete the file\\n- **IMPLEMENT**: `rm backend/database.py`\\n- **VALIDATE**: `python -c \\\"import backend.database\\\"` should raise `ModuleNotFoundError`\\n\\n### Task 6: Run full test suite\\n\\n- **ACTION**: Run all backend tests\\n- **IMPLEMENT**: `cd backend && python -m pytest tests/ -x -q 2>&1 | tail -20`\\n- **EXPECT**: All tests pass, zero failures\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Key Model Classes (reference when converting raw SQL to ORM)\\n\\nRead `backend/db_models.py` for the full list. Key models for test conversions:\\n\\n| Raw SQL table | SQLModel class | Key fields |\\n|---------------|---------------|------------|\\n| `things` | `ThingRecord` | id, title, thing_type, user_id, active, importance |\\n| `thing_relationships` | `ThingRelationshipRecord` | id, from_thing_id, to_thing_id, relationship_type |\\n| `users` | `UserRecord` | id, email, google_id, name |\\n| `chat_messages` | `ChatMessageRecord` | id, user_id, role, content, conversation_id |\\n| `conversation_summaries` | `ConversationSummaryRecord` | id, user_id, summary, message_count |\\n| `sweep_results` | `SweepResultRecord` | id, user_id, thing_id, ... |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Testing Strategy\\n\\n### Validation After Each Test File\\n\\n```bash\\ncd /mnt/ext-fast/.archon/worktrees/ext-fast/reli/archon/task-archon-fix-github-issue-1776496471739\\ncd backend && python -m pytest tests/<filename>.py -x -q 2>&1 | tail -10\\n```\\n\\n### Full Suite\\n\\n```bash\\ncd backend && python -m pytest tests/ -q 2>&1 | tail -20\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Validation Commands\\n\\n### Level 1: STATIC_ANALYSIS\\n\\n```bash\\ncd backend\\ngrep -rn \\\"from backend.database\\\\|from .database import db\\\\|import database\\\" tests/ --include=\\\"*.py\\\" | grep -v \\\"__pycache__\\\"\\n```\\n\\n**EXPECT**: Zero results (no remaining database.py imports)\\n\\n### Level 2: UNIT_TESTS\\n\\n```bash\\ncd backend && python -m pytest tests/ -x -q 2>&1 | tail -20\\n```\\n\\n**EXPECT**: All tests pass\\n\\n### Level 3: IMPORT CHECK\\n\\n```bash\\npython -c \\\"import backend.db_engine; print('db_engine OK')\\\"\\npython -c \\\"import backend.database\\\" 2>&1 | grep -c \\\"ModuleNotFoundError\\\"\\n```\\n\\n**EXPECT**: First prints `db_engine OK`, second prints `1`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Acceptance Criteria\\n\\n- [ ] `backend/database.py` is deleted\\n- [ ] `init_sqlmodel_tables()` removed from `db_engine.py`\\n- [ ] Zero `from backend.database import db` imports remain\\n- [ ] `conftest.py` no longer references `backend.database`\\n- [ ] All backend tests pass\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Completion Checklist\\n\\n- [ ] Task 1: `init_sqlmodel_tables()` removed from `db_engine.py`\\n- [ ] Task 2: `conftest.py` updated (no `db_module` import, `session_db` fixture added)\\n- [ ] Task 3: All 18 test files converted (validate each immediately)\\n- [ ] Task 4: Zero remaining `database.py` imports confirmed\\n- [ ] Task 5: `database.py` deleted\\n- [ ] Task 6: Full test suite passes\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Risks and Mitigations\\n\\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\\n| Raw SQL queries use column names not present as ORM fields | MED | MED | Read `db_models.py` fully before each conversion; check field names match |\\n| Test helper functions pass `conn` as arg (not context manager) | MED | LOW | Refactor helper to accept `Session` instead of `conn`, or use `engine_module.engine` directly |\\n| `test_things.py` PRAGMA FK off — SQLModel session autoflushes before PRAGMA | LOW | MED | Use `text()` with `session.exec()` and `autoflush=False` session if needed |\\n| `test_summarization.py` uses raw SQL with cursor `.fetchone()` row access | HIGH | MED | Convert to ORM `.first()` and access fields by attribute, not index |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Notes\\n\\n- `database_supabase.py` does NOT exist in this codebase — nothing to remove.\\n- `_exec()` from `db_engine.py` does NOT exist — nothing to remove.\\n- `user_filter()` from `auth.py` does NOT exist — nothing to remove.\\n- The issue description's bullet points partially reflect an earlier state; the actual work is: test migration + delete `database.py` + remove `init_sqlmodel_tables()`.\\n- `conftest.py`'s `patched_db` already handles the SQLModel engine patching correctly — the only change needed is removing the `DB_PATH` monkeypatch since `database.py` will be gone.\\n- After deletion, `init_db()` is gone — but `main.py` already runs Alembic directly, so no call site needs updating.\\n\"}}"],"msg":"db.sqlite_query_failed"}
